<% content_for :title, "Unexpected value" %>
<h1>Unexpected value (422)</h1>
<p>
  <code>invalid_behavior</code> is set to <code>:raise</code>, so the policy
  rejected an out-of-set value instead of stripping it:
</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Attribute:</strong> <%= @error.attribute %></li>
  <li><strong>Value:</strong> <%= @error.value.inspect %></li>
  <li><strong>Allowed:</strong> <%= @error.expected.inspect %></li>
</ul>
<p><%= link_to "← Back to posts", posts_path %></p>
